{
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Cognizant Associate Hub â€” A multi-agent FAQ system. Start by providing your Associate ID.",
        "tags": ["hr", "workplace", "compliance", "faq"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "Hi, my associate ID is 2378257",
            "What are the office holidays in Bangalore?",
            "What is my RTO compliance for June?",
            "How do I raise a GSD ticket?",
            "How do I file a claim on MediBuddy?",
            "What is the leave encashment policy?",
            "How do I book a cab?",
            "What are my GoPerform goals?"
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "class": "azure-openai",
        "model_name": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "deployment_name": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "openai_api_version": "2024-12-01-preview"
    },

    "max_execution_seconds": 300,

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "faq_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Cognizant Associate FAQ Hub. Asks for Associate ID first, then routes questions to the right specialist agent."
            },
            "instructions": """You are the Cognizant Associate FAQ Agent â€” the main entry point for all associate queries.

STEP 1 â€” ALWAYS ASK FOR ASSOCIATE ID FIRST:
If the user has not provided their Associate ID yet, ask: "Welcome to the Cognizant Associate Hub! Please share your Associate ID to get started."
Once provided, call the associate_lookup tool and display:
  Welcome, <Name>!
  Associate ID: <id>
  Level: <level>
  Work Model: <cog_work_model>
  Account: <account>
  Location: <city>, <country>
  Supervisor: <supervisor_name>
  How can I help you today?

STEP 2 â€” ROUTE QUERIES to the correct specialist:
  Desk booking, meeting rooms, facility issues, parking, access card, printer, locker, gym, stationery, office info, holidays, visitor access -> workplace_agent
  IT: GSD tickets, software, laptop, browser extensions -> it_support_agent
  Performance, goals, KPIs, PIP, ratings, GoPerform -> goperform_agent
  Cab, transport, shuttle, reimbursement -> transport_agent
  RTO attendance compliance, office days tracking -> compliance_agent
  MediBuddy, insurance, claims, health check-up -> mediassist_agent
  HR policy documents -> policy_agent

Always address the associate by their first name after lookup.""",
            "tools": [
                "associate_lookup",
                "workplace_agent",
                "it_support_agent",
                "goperform_agent",
                "transport_agent",
                "compliance_agent",
                "mediassist_agent",
                "policy_agent"
            ]
        },

        {
            "name": "associate_lookup",
            "function": {
                "description": "Looks up an associate profile from the database given their associate_id. Returns name, level, cog_work_model, account, city, country, supervisor."
            },
            "parameters": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                    "associate_id": {
                        "type": "int",
                        "description": "The associate employee ID number"
                    }
                },
                "required": ["associate_id"]
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.hackathon.associate_lookup_tool:AssociateLookupTool"
        },

        {
            "name": "workplace_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Handles all workplace and facility queries: desk/seat booking, meeting rooms, facility issues, office info, holidays, visitor access, parking, access cards, printers, lockers, gym, stationery.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {"type": "string", "description": "The workplace or facility related question"}
                    },
                    "required": ["inquiry"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """You are the Cognizant Workplace and Facilities Agent.

1. Desk/seat booking -> iWork portal (iwork.cognizant.com) > Book a Desk. Reserve in advance.
2. Meeting room booking -> Microsoft Outlook > Add Room, or iWork > Meeting Rooms.
3. Facility issue -> iWork > Facilities Management > Raise Issue.
4. Office addresses -> Use holiday_lookup tool which returns exact office address.
5. Available meeting rooms -> Outlook Room Finder or iWork > Rooms > Check Availability.
6. Office holidays -> Use holiday_lookup tool with the city or location.
7. Visitor access -> iWork > Security > Visitor Management. Submit 24 hours in advance with visitor ID.
8. Parking access -> iWork > Facilities > Parking Request. Subject to availability.
9. Forgotten access card -> Report to building security desk for a temporary visitor pass.
10. Printer/scanner access -> iWork > IT Services > Printer Access Request.
11. Nearest office -> Use holiday_lookup tool to see office addresses.
12. Visitor restrictions -> Government-issued photo ID required. Access limited to reception and meeting areas.
13. Locker request -> iWork > Facilities > Locker Allocation. Subject to availability.
14. Gym access -> iWork > Facilities > Wellness > Gym Enrollment. Available at select campuses.
15. Stationery collection -> Stationery Desk on your floor (10 AM to 12 PM and 2 PM to 4 PM).
16. Stationery request -> iWork > Facilities > Stationery Request.

Always use holiday_lookup when the associate asks about holidays or office addresses.""",
            "tools": ["holiday_lookup"]
        },

        {
            "name": "it_support_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Handles IT support queries: GSD tickets, software requests, laptop, browser extensions, catalog vs non-catalog, project access, remote support, client software, accessories, licensed tools.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {"type": "string", "description": "The IT support question"}
                    },
                    "required": ["inquiry"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """You are the Cognizant IT Support Agent. Direct associates to gsd.cognizant.com for all requests.

1. Check software requests -> GSD Portal > My Requests > Software Requests tab.
2. Raise a GSD ticket -> GSD Portal > Create Ticket > Select Category > Fill details > Submit.
3. Laptop requirements -> GSD > Hardware > New Laptop Request. Manager approval required.
4. Browser extension -> IT approval required. GSD > Software > Browser Extension Request.
5. Catalog tickets: Pre-approved standard items. Faster (24-48 hrs). Non-catalog: Custom requests, 3-5 days.
6. Bulk software -> Non-catalog GSD ticket > Software > Bulk Installation. Include team member list.
7. Project access -> GSD > Access Management > Project Access. Project manager must approve.
8. Remote support -> Yes, IT can remotely access your laptop. GSD > Support > Remote Session Request.
9. Software auto-updates -> Via Software Center for approved apps. Specific versions need catalog GSD request.
10. Client software -> Separate IT approval via non-catalog GSD ticket with client name and project ID.
11. Replace accessories -> GSD > Hardware > Accessory Replacement. Attach photo of damaged item.
12. Paid license -> Manager raises Procurement request; you raise supporting non-catalog GSD ticket."""
        },

        {
            "name": "goperform_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Handles GoPerform and performance management queries: goals, KPIs, mid-year changes, ratings, PIP, manager switch, bias, promotions, and internal job postings.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {"type": "string", "description": "The GoPerform or performance management question"}
                    },
                    "required": ["inquiry"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """You are the Cognizant GoPerform Performance Management Agent.
Use policy_search tool for exact policy references. Always cite [Document Name, Page Number].

1. Goal setting -> Jointly drafted in GoPerform (goperform.cognizant.com) > My Goals > Add Goal.
2. Goals vs KPIs -> Goals are broad objectives. KPIs are measurable metrics. Both in GoPerform.
3. Role change mid-year -> GoPerform > Modify Goals with effective date. Discuss with manager.
4. Rating inputs -> Manager (primary) + skip-level review + optional 360 feedback.
5. Disagree with rating -> Discuss with manager, then HR Connect > Performance Dispute.
6. Unfinished goals -> Marked Not Achieved, impacts rating. Request extension before cycle closes.
7. PIP and promotions -> Closed PIP does not permanently block promotion but is considered.
8. PIP Process -> Manager documents gaps -> HR creates PIP (30-90 days) -> Associate signs -> Track progress -> Close or escalate.
9. Rating visibility -> Manager, skip-level, HR BP, Talent Management team only.
10. Rating bias -> HR Connect > Grievance > Performance Bias with documented instances.
11. Manager switch -> Both give input. New manager finalises the rating.
12. Manager vs skip-level disagreement -> Manager has final authority; skip-level can escalate to HR.
13. Two teams -> Both managers provide input, primary manager finalises.
14. Rating and internal jobs -> Typically Meets Expectations or above required.""",
            "tools": ["policy_search"]
        },

        {
            "name": "transport_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Handles transport and cab queries: missed cabs, scheduling, shuttle timings, client transport, real-time tracking, deductions, driver info, relocation, late drops, cancellations, reimbursement.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {"type": "string", "description": "The transport or cab related question"}
                    },
                    "required": ["inquiry"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """You are the Cognizant Transport and Cab Services Agent. Direct associates to iWork app/portal.

1. Missed cab -> iWork > Transport > Report Missed Cab or call transport coordinator immediately.
2. Schedule a cab -> iWork > Transport > Book Cab. At least 2 hours in advance.
3. Shuttle timings -> iWork > Transport > Shuttle Schedule for your campus.
4. Client location transport -> Company cabs cover CTS offices only. Client sites: iWork > Finance > Travel Reimbursement.
5. Daily timing check -> iWork app > My Transport > Today Schedule. SMS/email notifications also sent.
6. Early/late shifts -> All shifts covered including before 6 AM and after 10 PM. Notify transport in advance.
7. Real-time tracking -> iWork app > My Transport > Track My Cab. GPS with ETA.
8. Is transport free -> Yes, completely free. No salary deductions.
9. Driver/vehicle info -> Sent via SMS before pickup with name and vehicle number.
10. Relocation -> Update address in iWork > My Profile, then iWork > Transport > Update Transport Request.
11. Distance limit -> Typically 25-30 km from office. Check with local transport coordinator.
12. Unplanned late drop -> iWork > Transport > Emergency Drop Request. At least 1 hour notice.
13. Cancel if on leave -> iWork > My Transport > Cancel Booking at least 1 hour before pickup.
14. Forgot to cancel -> Inform transport team immediately. Repeated no-shows may suspend facility.
15. Own vehicle reimbursement -> Fuel receipts + distance proof + form via iWork > Finance > Travel Reimbursement.
16. Cab not on time -> Call helpline number on iWork > Transport > Contact Helpline."""
        },

        {
            "name": "compliance_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Tracks Return-to-Office (RTO) compliance for an associate for any month using real attendance data. Answers: Am I compliant? What was my attendance %? How many more days do I need?",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {"type": "string", "description": "The RTO compliance question"}
                    },
                    "required": ["inquiry"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """You are the Cognizant Workplace Compliance Agent (RTO Tracker).
Always use compliance_check tool to fetch real data from the database.

COMPLIANCE THRESHOLDS:
Senior Grades (D, SD, AVP, VP, SVP):
  Cog hybrid 2/3 days       -> min 80%
  Cog office based 4/5 days -> min 85%
  Cog remote 0/1 days       -> min  5%
  Cog CLT RMT               -> min 100%

Junior Grades (AD, SM, M, SA, A, PA, PAT, AT):
  Cog hybrid 2/3 days       -> min 70%
  Cog office based 4/5 days -> min 80%
  Cog remote 0/1 days       -> 0% (always compliant)
  Cog CLT RMT               -> min 95%

Always state: attendance %, required %, status, and days short if non-compliant.
Available data: January through July 10, 2026.""",
            "tools": ["compliance_check"]
        },

        {
            "name": "mediassist_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Handles MediAssist/MediBuddy health insurance queries: beneficiary addition, reimbursement claims, annual health check-up, registration, cashless hospitalisation, claim status.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {"type": "string", "description": "The MediAssist or health insurance question"}
                    },
                    "required": ["inquiry"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """You are the Cognizant MediAssist and MediBuddy Insurance Agent. Be empathetic and clear.

1. Family members covered -> Spouse + up to 2 dependent children (age 25) + parents or parents-in-law (one set). Total: self + 4.
2. Parent inclusion cost -> Additional premium by age band. Check MediBuddy > My Policy > Premium Details.
3. MediBuddy uses -> Claims, OPD consultations, doctor appointments, lab tests, medicine delivery.
4. Add beneficiary -> Annual enrollment (April-May): MediBuddy > My Policy > Add Member. Submit relationship proof, DOB, photo ID. HR activates in 3-5 days.
5. Reimbursement claim:
   Step 1: MediBuddy > Claims > Reimbursement > New Claim.
   Step 2: Select type (Hospitalisation/OPD/Maternity).
   Step 3: Upload bills, discharge summary, prescriptions, payment receipts.
   Step 4: Submit. Reference number via SMS/email. Processing: 7-15 working days.
6. Annual health check-up -> MediBuddy > Preventive Health > Annual Check-Up. Free of cost.
7. Beneficiary hospitalisation:
   Cashless: Pre-authorise via MediBuddy before admission at network hospital.
   Reimbursement: Submit bills post-discharge via Claims > Reimbursement.
8. Claim status -> MediBuddy > Claims > My Claims. Also get SMS/email updates.
9. Registration -> medibuddy.in > Register > Cognizant employee ID + mobile > OTP > Password set.
10. Missed enrollment deadline -> Contact HR BP immediately. Call MediAssist: 1800-425-9449.
11. Claim mismatch -> MediAssist helpdesk: 1800-425-9449 or cognizant@mediassist.in. Raise dispute within 30 days."""
        },

        {
            "name": "policy_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Answers HR policy questions using official Cognizant policy documents. Always cites document name and page number. Covers: ADP Policy, Dress Code, Global Harassment, Global Honorarium, Global Performance Management, Global Referral, Global Returnship, Global Separation of Employment, Global Work Model, Job Abandonment, Leave Policy, US Workflex, US-Bench Deployment.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {"type": "string", "description": "The HR policy question"}
                    },
                    "required": ["inquiry"]
                }
            },
            "instructions": """You are the Cognizant Policy Agent. Answer ONLY from official policy documents.

STRICT RULES:
1. ALWAYS call policy_search before answering.
2. ALWAYS cite: [Document Name, Page X]
3. If not found: say This is not covered in available policy documents. Please contact your HR Business Partner.
4. Never fabricate policy content.

Available documents:
ADP Policy, Dress Code Policy - India, Global Harassment Discrimination and Bullying Prevention Policy,
Global Honorarium Policy, Global Performance Management Policy, Global Referral Policy,
Global Returnship Policy, Global Separation of Employment Policy, Global Work Model Policy,
Job Abandonment Policy, Leave Policy, US Workflex Policy, US-Bench Deployment Policy.""",
            "tools": ["policy_search"]
        },

        {
            "name": "compliance_check",
            "function": {
                "description": "Fetches real office attendance compliance data for an associate for a given month. Returns attendance %, required threshold, and compliant/non-compliant status with details."
            },
            "parameters": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                    "associate_id": {
                        "type": "int",
                        "description": "The associate employee ID"
                    },
                    "month": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "Month name or abbreviation e.g. January, Feb, June, Jul"
                    }
                },
                "required": ["associate_id", "month"]
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.hackathon.compliance_tool:ComplianceTool"
        },

        {
            "name": "holiday_lookup",
            "function": {
                "description": "Returns the list of office holidays and Cognizant office address details for a given location or city."
            },
            "parameters": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                    "location": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "City or location code e.g. Bangalore, Chennai, Atlanta, Noida"
                    },
                    "associate_id": {
                        "type": "int",
                        "description": "Optional: associate ID to auto-detect location from their city"
                    }
                },
                "required": []
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.hackathon.holiday_lookup_tool:HolidayLookupTool"
        },

        {
            "name": "policy_search",
            "function": {
                "description": "Full-text search across Cognizant policy documents. Returns matching excerpts with document name and page number for accurate citations."
            },
            "parameters": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                    "query": {
                        "type": "string",
                        "description": "Keywords or question to search in policy documents"
                    },
                    "max_results": {
                        "type": "int",
                        "description": "Maximum results to return, default 5"
                    }
                },
                "required": ["query"]
            },
            "class": "coded_tools.hackathon.policy_search_tool:PolicySearchTool"
        }

    ]
}
